This repository contains Python packaging, API, plotting examples, and orchestration code for master-equation workflows with initial system-environment correlations.

It also packages curated scientific inputs and original Fortran solver sources that are preserved for reproducibility and provenance.

Bundled research materials are included as part of the software record associated with:

Ali Raza Mirza, Muhammad Zia, and Adam Zaman Chaudhry,
"A master equation incorporating the system-environment correlations present in the joint equilibrium state",
arXiv:2012.14853
https://arxiv.org/abs/2012.14853

The MIT license in this repository applies to the package code unless a bundled file or upstream provenance note says otherwise.
